This paper deals with secure communication in fading channels, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of relays, which is a common technique in wireless networks and falls under the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper analyzes the impact of the number of antennas on the secrecy performance, which is a topic that falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents numerical results, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
